  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Change in mean urine osmolality</measure>
    <time_frame>Baseline, 7 hours</time_frame>
    <description>Urine osmolality is a measure of urine concentration. Urine osmolality will be measured using a Wescor vapor pressure osmometer. A normal range for urine osmolality is approximately 500-850 mOsm/kg water. Change is the difference in average osmolality from baseline to 7 hours.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
